# =============================================================================
# NOTES
# =============================================================================

# 1. Database IDs are automatically generated as db_1, db_2, db_3, etc.
# 2. The system auto-discovers databases by scanning for DB_TYPE_* variables
# 3. Each database connection is completely independent - failures are isolated
# 4. You can mix and match any database types in any combination
# 5. Connection pooling and advanced settings are configured in src/constants.ts
# 6. Use switch_environment tool to change between databases at runtime
# 7. All existing MySQL tools work with the new architecture
# 8. Security settings apply globally but can be database-type specific
# 9. Always use SSL/TLS in production (DB_SSL_*=true)
# 10. Store sensitive credentials in environment-specific files, not in code